        "function": {
            "name": "activate_mcp_server_monitoring_tools",
            "description": "Call this tool when you need access to a new category of tools. The category of tools is described as follows:\n\nThis group of tools is focused on monitoring the status and health of MCP (Multi-Channel Processing) servers. The 'Get status of a specific MCP server or all servers' tool allows users to retrieve the current operational status of one or multiple servers, providing insights into their availability and performance. Meanwhile, the 'Perform health check on all or specific MCP servers' tool enables users to conduct thorough health assessments, identifying potential issues that could affect server functionality. Together, these tools facilitate proactive server management by allowing administrators to monitor server health and status in real-time, ensuring optimal performance and quick response to any issues that may arise.\n\nBe sure to call this tool if you need a capability related to the above."
