            "description": "Call this tool when you need access to a new category of tools. The category of tools is described as follows:\n\nThis group encompasses tools designed for managing the lifecycle of MCP servers, including launching, stopping, and restarting them. The 'Launch an MCP server in a separate console process' tool is essential for initiating new server instances, allowing users to expand their processing capabilities as needed. The 'Restart an MCP server (stop and start)' tool provides a straightforward method for refreshing server operations, which can be crucial for applying updates or resolving performance issues. Lastly, the 'Stop a running MCP server' tool allows for the graceful shutdown of servers when they are no longer needed. Collectively, these tools empower administrators to effectively manage server resources, ensuring that they can be deployed, maintained, and terminated as required to meet operational demands.\n\nBe sure to call this tool if you need a capability related to the above."
