    {
        "function": {
            "name": "activate_prolog_session_management_tools",
            "description": "Call this tool when you need access to a new category of tools. The category of tools is described as follows:\n\nThis group of tools is designed for managing Prolog sessions, which are essential for executing Prolog queries and handling knowledge bases in a structured manner. The tools allow users to create new sessions, load Prolog files into the session's knowledge base, list all active sessions, and execute queries within those sessions. This functionality is particularly useful for developers and researchers working with Prolog, as it facilitates the organization and manipulation of logical data and rules.\n\nThe 'mcp_prolog-mcp-se_prolog_create_session' tool initiates a new Prolog session, providing a clean environment for users to work on specific projects or queries. Once a session is created, users can utilize the 'mcp_prolog-mcp-se_prolog_consult_file' tool to load Prolog files, which contain facts and rules that the session can use to answer queries or perform logical deductions.\n\nTo keep track of ongoing work, the 'mcp_prolog-mcp-se_prolog_list_sessions' tool allows users to view all active Prolog sessions. This is particularly beneficial in scenarios where multiple projects or experiments are being conducted simultaneously, as it helps in managing resources effectively.\n\nFinally, the 'mcp_prolog-mcp-se_prolog_query' tool enables users to execute specific queries within the selected session. This is where the power of Prolog comes into play, allowing users to retrieve information, infer new knowledge, or validate logical statements based on the loaded data.\n\nTogether, these tools create a cohesive environment for working with Prolog, making it easier to manage sessions, load necessary data, and perform complex queries, thereby enhancing productivity and efficiency in logical programming tasks.\n\nBe sure to call this tool if you need a capability related to the above."
        },
        "type": "function"
    },
