    {
        "function": {
            "name": "activate_prolog_rule_persistence_tools",
            "description": "Call this tool when you need access to a new category of tools. The category of tools is described as follows:\n\nThis group of tools is designed for the management of Prolog rules within a SQLite database, focusing on the loading and saving of rules to and from a session knowledge base. The tools enable users to persistently store Prolog rules, ensuring that important logic and knowledge can be reused across sessions. By loading rules from the database, users can quickly access previously defined logic, enhancing the efficiency of their Prolog applications. The ability to save rules back to the database allows for dynamic updates and modifications to the knowledge base, making it easier to maintain and evolve the logic as needed. Together, these tools provide a robust framework for managing Prolog rules in a structured and persistent manner.\n\nBe sure to call this tool if you need a capability related to the above."
