###  6.1   [Navigate to header](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/2025-06-18/server/resources#https://) https://

Used to represent a resource available on the web.Servers SHOULD use this scheme only when the client is able to fetch and load the resource
directly from the web on its ownâ€”that is, it doesnâ€™t need to read the resource via
the MCP server.For other use cases, servers SHOULD prefer to use another URI scheme, or define a custom one, even if the server
will itself be downloading resource contents over the internet.
