###  6.2   [Navigate to header](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/specification/2025-06-18/server/resources#file://) file://

Used to identify resources that behave like a filesystem. However, the resources
do not need to map to an actual physical filesystem.MCP servers MAY identify file:// resources with an [XDG MIME type](https://specifications.freedesktop.org/shared-mime-info-spec/0.14/ar01s02.html#id-1.3.14), like `inode/directory`, to represent non-regular files (such as directories) that donâ€™t otherwise have
a standard MIME type.
